5|$|In {{traditional}} Chinese medicine cubeb is {{used for}} its alleged warming property. In <b>Tibetan</b> medicine, cubeb (ka ko la in <b>Tibetan)</b> is one of bzang po drug, six fine herbs beneficial to specific organs in the body, with cubeb assigned to the spleen.|$|E
